\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"A metadata-only fix did not resolve `ant:ant:1.6`.\\n\\nI reproduced the failure with:\\n\\n```bash\\nGVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6\\n```\\n\\nIt still fails in `ant.ant.ClassConstantsTest#readInitializesByteArrayParameterTypeInFreshAntClassLoader` with:\\n\\n```text\\njava.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.tools.ant.filters.ClassConstants\\n```\\n\\nI traced a native run with `runNativeTraceImage` and checked the generated trace metadata. The important result is that this is not surfacing as a `Missing*RegistrationError`, and the trace does not show a resource access for `org/apache/tools/ant/filters/ClassConstants.class`. That points to the failure happening in the isolated `AntClassLoader` path before the current reachability-metadata entries can help. I also tried targeted resource and reflection-array additions, verified they did not change the reproducer, and removed those speculative edits.\\n\\nThe current evidence says this is likely a native runtime classpath / `AntClassLoader` behavior issue rather than a missing `reachability-metadata.json` entry. If you want, I can continue by debugging the native runtime classpath handling for this test or by adjusting the `ant` test fixture instead of the metadata.\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
